c: 18
v: 19
t: "And so We awakened them so that they might question one another. One of them exclaimed, ‚ÄúHow long have you remained ňĻasleepňļ?‚ÄĚ Some replied, ‚ÄúPerhaps a day, or part of a day.‚ÄĚ They said ňĻto one anotherňļ, ‚ÄúYour Lord knows best how long you have remained. So send one of you with these silver coins of yours to the city, and let him find which food is the purest, and then bring you provisions from it. Let him be ňĻexceptionallyňļ cautious, and do not let him give you away"